  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. A screening sensitivity exercise was conducted internally to rank input parameters by influence on construct stiffness and yield force; titanium alloy elastic modulus and cortical fixation depth were identified as the dominant drivers. These findings informed the acceptance bounds and the experimental design but are documented only in the engineering notebook; no formal SensitivityAnalysis node has been registered in this package.",
