      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI change < 2% between successive refinement levels.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh convergence study was performed on the screw-rod interface region (coarse: ~180 k elements; medium: ~410 k; fine: ~920 k). Construct stiffness changed by 1.4% from medium to fine; yield force changed by 0.9%. The medium mesh was selected for production runs, achieving Gradation 3 through systematic convergence demonstration exceeding the required Gradation 2."
