  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors were assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required gradation level for a Medium assurance, Model Risk Level 3 assessment. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted because ASTM F1717 defines the regulatory reference standard for pedicle screw mechanical testing, only one test condition is specified in that standard, and the decision consequence is Medium rather than High. All five quantitative validation comparisons satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percentage difference < 10%. The credibility evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory submission claim that the FEA framework reliably predicts compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
